@node IntroductionNode "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}
@{b}============@{ub}

FamilyTree is an add on to Scion Genealogist to print out graphical family
trees.

It is also able to display the same family tree graphic on the screen.

It requires OS 2.04 or higher and Scion Genealogist 4.09 (available on
Aminet).

If you plan to print out the family tree then you will require a graphics
capable printer and printer driver.

Why did I bother?

My mother-in-law had a family tree printout which she obtained at a family
reunion.  Obviously families are dynamic things and she planned to make the
update to the family tree by hand.  However, the original formatting of the
family tree did not leave room for any additions.

I suggested to my wife that we find a public domain genealogy program to
enter the current family data into.  Then it would be possible to keep it
up to date and create printouts whenever needed.  I found Scion Genealogist
but was disappointed to discover that it did not support graphical family
tree printouts.

To address our need I have developed FamilyTree.  I hope you find this to be
a useful addition to the excellent Scion Genealogist.  If you have any
comments or suggestions please do not hesitate to contact me.

Timothy Fagan

tfagan@kpmg.com
@endnode
@node InstallationNode "Installation"
@{b}Installation@{ub}
@{b}============@{ub}

The FamilyTree archive (familytree.lha) contains:

o  FamilyTree and FamilyTree.info

o  FTStack.rexx

o  FamilyTree.guide and FamilyTree.guide.info

o  familytree.readme

all within the directory FamilyTree.

Unarchive familytree.lha in the Scion Genealogist directory and it is ready
to use.

I recommend you assign FamilyTree to one of the function keys in Scion
Genealogist.  To do this:

o  start Scion Genealogist,

o  go to menu option "Set Function Keys" in the "Prefs" menu,

o  click in the box next to the function key you wish to assign it to and
   enter FamilyTree/FamilyTree,

o  click "Accept",

o  choose menu option "Save" in the "Prefs" menu.

Pressing the selected function key should now run FamilyTree.

Using the @{"command line options" link CommandLineUsageNode } it is 
possible to set
up function keys to perform automatic printing and previewing,
for example "FamilyTree/FamilyTree preview".
@endnode
@node CommandLineUsageNode "Command Line Usage"
@{b}Command Line Usage@{ub}
@{b}==================@{ub}

Family Tree may be run from a CLI.  Its template is:

   FamilyTree FN=FontName/K,FS=FontSize/K/N,D=Density/K/N,
      LAN=Landscape/S,POR=Portrait/S,SM=ScreenMode/K/N,
      PT=Print/S,PV=Preview/S

FontName is the name of the font (including the suffix ".font") to use when
rendering the family tree.

FontSize is the font size to use when rendering the family tree.

Density is the printer density to use in printing the family tree.  Valid
values are 1 to 7.

Landscape rotates the image by 90 degrees before printing it, such that when
a printed page is held with the family tree the correct way up, it is wider
than it is tall.

Portrait does not rotate the image.  The page is taller than it is
wide.

ScreenMode is the decimal value which identifies the screen mode to be used
for previews.  This is not a lot of use but is there for completeness.

Print suppresses the normal FamilyTree GUI (except for error messages and
progress/cancel requesters) and automatically prints the family tree
starting at the person currently selected in Scion Genealogist.

Preview suppresses the normal FamilyTree GUI (except for error messages)
and automatically previews the family tree starting at the person currently
selected in Scion Genealogist.

Any unspecified parameters are defaulted first from any saved FamilyTree
preferences, or if these are not found, from other system preferences.

If you do not specify either Print or Preview then the @{"GUI"
link GUIUsageNode} will be displayed.
@endnode
@node GUIUsageNode "GUI Usage"
@{b}GUI Usage@{ub}
@{b}=========@{ub}

The FamilyTree GUI is divided into four sections:

o  Font

o  Print

o  Preview

o  Actions

The Font section allows you to specify a font (name and size) to be used
in rendering the family tree.  It also shows how many pixels wide and tall
the family tree will be in the selected font.

The Print section allows you to specify the density and aspect in which to
print the family tree.  It also shows how many pixels wide and high a
printed page will be, how many pages wide and high the printed family tree
will be, and the total number of pages required.

The Preview section allows you to specify the screen mode to be used in
previewing the family tree.

The Actions section has buttons to:

o  Print

o  Preview

o  Save Prefs

o  Cancel

The Print button begins printing the family tree.  Printing may be cancelled
by clicking on the cancel button on the print progress requester.

The Preview button displays the family tree (memory permitting) on the
screen.  The family tree preview may be scrolled around by moving the mouse
and exited by pressing either mouse button.

The Save Prefs button saves the font, density, aspect and screen mode as
preferences for the next time FamilyTree is run.

The Cancel button exits from FamilyTree.

The FamilyTree GUI @{b}is@{ub} font adaptive, but it opens on the Scion
Genealogist screen which always uses the 8 point topaz font.
@endnode
@node FamilyTreeGraphicNode "Family Tree Graphic"
@{b}Family Tree Graphic@{ub}
@{b}===================@{ub}

The rendered family tree starts from the currently selected person and works
down through the spouses and children.

Each person is represented by a rectangular box which contains four lines of
data:

o  Family Name

o  Given Names

o  Date of Birth

o  Date of Death

If any of these values is not recorded in Scion Genealogist for a person,
then the line is left blank.

Each box is the same size (I think it looks better that way) and the width
is determined by the widest box required within the family tree.

Marriages are shown by the letter "M" in the line connecting two people. The
date of the start of the marriage is shown to the left of the "M" and the
date of the end of the marriage (if any) is shown to the right of the "M".

People are centred over their spouses and children.

All text is done in the selected font.
@endnode
