@node TroubleShootingNode "Trouble Shooting"
@{b}Trouble Shooting@{ub}
@{b}================@{ub}

Here are some difficulties you may encounter using FamilyTree:

When trying to preview a large family tree you may receive the message
"Unable to open screen".  This is most likely to be a result of not having
enough contiguous chip memory to open the screen.  To get around this
problem either chose a smaller font, preview a smaller part of the family
tree or free up some chip memory from other applications.

The first thing that FamilyTree does when it is run is to load the family
tree starting at the currently selected person in Scion Genealogist.  With
large family trees it is possible to run out of stack space, which is likely
to result in a Guru.  My solution to this was to write the rexx program
FTStack.rexx which accepts an additional parameter of a new stack size.
For example I have set up a Scion Genealogist function key with
"FamilyTree/FTStack.rexx 100000 preview" which handles the largest family
tree I use. NOTE: This error is @{i}still@{ui} occurring despite the work around!

FamilyTree does not handle a person marrying the same person twice.

FamilyTree does not handle loops in families (eg. incest or marrying your
brother's widow).

If your printer driver tells FamilyTree how many dots there are down the
length of the page then it uses it.  Otherwise it calculates it from the
number of lines per page, the number of lines per inch and the number of
dots per inch.  If you have set the number of lines per page incorrectly
it will get the wrong answer.
@endnode
@node BugsNode "Bugs"
@{b}Bugs@{ub}
@{b}====@{ub}

FamilyTree has been tested on the following systems:

o  A1200 + 68060/50 (Blizzard 1260) + 18MB RAM + Cannon BJ10sx

Here is a list of known bugs and things to do:

Type Severity Description
==== ======== ===========
BUG     High  Falls over on very large family trees - i thought it may be
              the stack but FTStack.rexx does not seem to fix it!?
BUG     Med   Max inner box width should not include marriage date in its
              calculation, it looks silly sometimes
TO DO   Med   Sort so that children and marriages read chronologically
              left to right
TO DO   Med   Control GUI from keyboard as well
TO DO   Low   Avoid loops in families (inbred, incest, etc.)
TO DO   Low   Should not lock Scion Genealogist screen as a handy rastport
TO DO   Low   RenderPersonToRastPort() only if outer box intersects
              rastport
TO DO   Low   Remove ".font" from fonts on the GUI
TO DO   Low   Multi-screen preview if not enough chip RAM to preview on a
              single screen
TO DO   Low   Allow selective page printing and suppress blank pages
TO DO   Low   Locale support
@endnode
